---
const title = "Layered Graphics — headless graphics for every app";
const description = "A FOSS, browser-first engine for Photoshop-like graphics authoring in applications, scripts, and AI-agent workflows.";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:title" content={title} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:image" content="/readme-banner.png" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="data:image/svg+xml,<svg xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22 viewBox=%220 0 64 64%22><rect width=%2264%22 height=%2264%22 fill=%22%237548ff%22/><path d=%22M10 27h44v10H10zM27 10h10v44H27z%22 fill=%22white%22/></svg>" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header>
      <a class="brand" href="/">Layered Graphics</a>
      <nav aria-label="Primary">
        <a href="/docs/">Docs</a>
        <a href="/playground/">Browser proof</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/iamkaf/layeredgraphics">GitHub</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="eyebrow">FOSS · browser-first · agent-friendly</div>
        <h1>Photoshop-like graphics authoring, embedded anywhere.</h1>
        <p>{description}</p>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="primary" href="/docs/">Get started</a>
          <a href="/playground/">Render the document in your browser</a>
        </div>
        <figure>
          <img src="/readme-banner.png" width="1200" height="630" alt="Layered Graphics banner generated by the engine itself" />
          <figcaption>This banner is an editable <code>.kgfx</code> document built and rendered entirely through the public <code>lg</code> CLI.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </section>

      <section class="pillars" aria-label="Core workflows">
        <article><span>01</span><h2>Embed an editor</h2><p>Bring layers, transforms, painting, masks, tools, and history into an application without adopting a prescribed UI.</p></article>
        <article><span>02</span><h2>Automate production</h2><p>Build portable documents, execute operation arrays, inspect their structure, and render authoritative output from scripts.</p></article>
        <article><span>03</span><h2>Give agents a canvas</h2><p>A compact CLI lets an agent create, inspect, render, visually evaluate, and revise complete compositions.</p></article>
      </section>

      <section class="terminal" aria-label="CLI example">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">One command language</div>
          <h2>Human-friendly. Machine-readable.</h2>
          <p>The imperative SDK and CLI compile to the same validated operations. The document stays editable and every runtime sees the same canonical state.</p>
        </div>
        <pre><code>lg new banner.kgfx --width 1200 --height 630
lg asset add banner.kgfx --id hero ./hero.png
lg layer add banner.kgfx --type image --asset-id hero
lg render banner.kgfx -o banner.png</code></pre>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer>Layered Graphics is being built in the open.</footer>
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  :global(*) { box-sizing: border-box; }
  :global(html) { background: #090d18; color: #f4f7ff; font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; }
  :global(body) { margin: 0; background: radial-gradient(circle at 80% 10%, #211852 0, transparent 30rem), #090d18; }
  a { color: inherit; }
  header { max-width: 1200px; margin: auto; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .brand { font-weight: 800; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: -.03em; }
  nav { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; color: #b7c1d9; font-size: .95rem; }
  nav a { text-decoration: none; }
  nav a:hover { color: #fff; }
  main { max-width: 1200px; margin: auto; padding: 5rem 2rem 7rem; }
  .hero { text-align: center; }
  .eyebrow { color: #34e1c5; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .14em; font-weight: 700; font-size: .78rem; }
  h1 { max-width: 950px; margin: 1.25rem auto; font-size: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6.2rem); line-height: .98; letter-spacing: -.065em; }
  .hero > p { max-width: 720px; margin: 1.5rem auto; color: #b7c1d9; font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.65; }
  .actions { display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 1rem; align-items: center; margin: 2.25rem 0 4rem; }
  .actions a { padding: .9rem 1.2rem; border: 1px solid #4a5b80; border-radius: .55rem; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }
  .actions .primary { background: #7548ff; border-color: #7548ff; }
  figure { margin: 0; border: 1px solid #202b42; padding: .75rem; border-radius: 1rem; background: #0d1320; box-shadow: 0 2rem 6rem #0008; }
  figure img { display: block; width: 100%; height: auto; border-radius: .5rem; }
  figcaption { color: #77829d; margin: .9rem .25rem .15rem; font-size: .9rem; }
  .pillars { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1rem; margin: 7rem 0; }
  article { padding: 2rem; border: 1px solid #202b42; background: #0d1320bb; border-radius: .75rem; }
  article span { color: #8f6dff; font-family: monospace; }
  article h2 { margin: 2.5rem 0 .75rem; font-size: 1.3rem; }
  article p, .terminal p { color: #b7c1d9; line-height: 1.65; }
  .terminal { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.25fr; gap: 4rem; align-items: center; }
  .terminal h2 { font-size: 2.5rem; letter-spacing: -.04em; margin: .8rem 0; }
  pre { overflow: auto; padding: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid #202b42; border-radius: .75rem; background: #050812; color: #dce2f1; line-height: 1.7; }
  footer { text-align: center; color: #77829d; border-top: 1px solid #202b42; padding: 2rem; }
  @media (max-width: 760px) { nav a:nth-child(2) { display: none; } main { padding-top: 3rem; } .actions { flex-direction: column; } .pillars, .terminal { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .terminal { gap: 1rem; } }
</style>
